&lt;div class="post-text" itemprop="text"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;code&gt;genres&lt;/code&gt; is an &lt;a href="https://www.tutorialspoint.com/php/php_arrays.htm" rel="nofollow noreferrer"&gt;associative array&lt;/a&gt; meaning that the key will only give you the index point of that value. Your values are of type String, not numerical values.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code&gt;$genres = ['Adventure', 'Drama', 'Game', 'Harem', 'Martial Arts', 'Seinen'];
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;

&lt;p&gt;So in this case, at index point 0 (arrays start at 0), we will get Adventure.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code&gt;[0] =&amp;gt; Adventure
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;

&lt;p&gt;To get these values out of the array one by one you can do this:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code&gt;foreach($genres as $_genre) {
    echo $_genre;
}
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;

&lt;p&gt;To get these values and/or keys from the array one by one you can do this:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code&gt;foreach($genres as $_key =&amp;gt; $_genre) {
    echo "Index: {$_key} - Value: {$_genre}"
}
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Keys are numerical values, they mark the point of the value in that array. For example, if we wanted to get &lt;code&gt;Game&lt;/code&gt; from the array:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code&gt;[2] =&amp;gt; Game
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We can see that it has an index of 2 and can be called like:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code&gt;echo $genres[2];
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;

