&lt;p&gt;You could write a reverse router with javascript in which given a URL, it returns the parameters.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Example (really bad one, just to give you an idea) &lt;a href="http://jsfiddle.net/dgCfb/" rel="nofollow"&gt;on jsfiddle&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Drawbacks: you will have to copy the routings from &lt;code&gt;.htacces&lt;/code&gt; file to Javascript. Everytime something changes in that file, you will have to change in Javascript too.&lt;/p&gt;

