&lt;div class="post-text" itemprop="text"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You can set default values when creating the table itself, but apart from that, the code you pasted is missing some brackets:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code&gt;INSERT INTO `tablename` (number) VALUES (" . $number.")";
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If you want to use a NULL when inserting and get a default value in the table, you can do it when creating the table like this:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code&gt;CREATE TABLE test 
    (
    id INT NOT NULL AUTO_INCREMENT, 
    someField VARCHAR(15) NOT NULL DEFAULT 'on'
    )
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Now when you try to insert data into it, you can do the following:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code&gt;insert into `tablename` (id, someField) values (null, null)
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;

&lt;p&gt;and get a row with an incremented ID and the string 'on' in the column &lt;code&gt;someField&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If you want to check for nulls when inserting data into a table, you can then use something like the following to ensure you have the value:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code&gt;$someField=(isset($number))?$number:'null';
INSERT INTO `tablename` (number) VALUES (" . $someField.")";
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This is assuming you have already verified that $number is either numeric or isn't submitted when sending the form.&lt;/p&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;

