Answer:
&lt;div class="post-text" itemprop="text"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Here is an SQL that will return what you want&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code&gt;mysql&amp;gt; CREATE TABLE sample (Start INT, End INT);

mysql&amp;gt; INSERT sample VALUES (9,12),(1,2),(60,88),(10,11),(79,80);

mysql&amp;gt; SELECT * 
    -&amp;gt; FROM sample s 
    -&amp;gt; WHERE NOT EXISTS (SELECT 1 
    -&amp;gt;                   FROM sample 
    -&amp;gt;                   WHERE s.Start &amp;gt; Start AND s.Start &amp;lt; End);
+-------+------+
| Start | End  |
+-------+------+
|     9 |   12 |
|     1 |    2 |
|    60 |   88 |
+-------+------+
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;

&lt;p&gt;You can, of course, create VIEW, move the data to another table or delete rows using the above SQL.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;NOTE: I am not really sure why are you doing this 'optimization'.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;EDIT:&lt;br&gt;
The query can be rewritten as&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code&gt;SELECT s.* 
FROM sample s LEFT JOIN 
     sample s2 ON s.Start &amp;gt; s2.Start AND s.Start &amp;lt; s2.End 
WHERE s2.start IS NULL;
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Which will create different execution plan (2xsimple select vs primary/dependent subquery for EXISTS), so performance might be different. Both queries will use an index on (Start, End) if it exists.&lt;/p&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;

&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code class="language-java"&gt;
&lt;span class="hljs-built_in"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="hljs-literal"&gt;[]&lt;/span&gt; ints &amp;#61; &lt;span class="hljs-module-access"&gt;&lt;span class="hljs-module"&gt;&lt;span class="hljs-identifier"&gt;Stream&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;iterate(&lt;span class="hljs-number"&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;, i -&amp;gt; i &amp;#43; &lt;span class="hljs-number"&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;).limit(&lt;span class="hljs-number"&gt;100&lt;/span&gt;).filter(i -&amp;gt; i % &lt;span class="hljs-number"&gt;2&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="hljs-operator"&gt; &amp;#61;&amp;#61; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="hljs-number"&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;).map&lt;span class="hljs-constructor"&gt;ToInt(&lt;span class="hljs-params"&gt;i&lt;/span&gt; -&amp;gt; &lt;span class="hljs-params"&gt;i&lt;/span&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;span class="hljs-keyword"&gt;to&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="hljs-constructor"&gt;Array()&lt;/span&gt;;
        &lt;span class="hljs-module-access"&gt;&lt;span class="hljs-module"&gt;&lt;span class="hljs-identifier"&gt;System&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;out.println(&lt;span class="hljs-module-access"&gt;&lt;span class="hljs-module"&gt;&lt;span class="hljs-identifier"&gt;Arrays&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="hljs-keyword"&gt;to&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="hljs-constructor"&gt;String(&lt;span class="hljs-params"&gt;ints&lt;/span&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;);
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;

&lt;div class="post-text" itemprop="text"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In your inner &lt;code&gt;foreach&lt;/code&gt; loop, the keys &lt;code&gt;label_size&lt;/code&gt;, &lt;code&gt;label_position&lt;/code&gt; and &lt;code&gt;label_qty&lt;/code&gt; don't exist. When a key doesn't exist, I guess it's defaulting to 0 and as a result just gives you the first letter. This will produce what you want:&lt;/p&gt;

